detial.description: Aviation and transport is a course that focuses on the study of transportation systems, with a particular emphasis on aviation. The course covers a wide range of topics related to aviation and transportation, including aircraft design, air traffic control, airport operations, logistics, and supply chain management.Students in this course typically study the principles of aerodynamics, aircraft systems, and aviation regulations. They may also learn about airport design, ground handling, and the management of air traffic control systems.
requirements: Professional Bachelor Degree in Aviation Transport and /or 5th Level Professional Qualification in Aviation Transport (2 years).
Bachelor Degree of Engineering Science in Mechanical Engineering (for studies majoring in Aviation Transport) or Electrical Engineering (for studies majoring in Avionics) (3 years).
